<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13661] KRaft uses the wrong permission for adding topic partitions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13661</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cmccabe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cmccabe&quot;&gt;cmccabe&lt;/a&gt; caught this as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13646&quot; title=&quot;Implement KIP-801: KRaft authorizer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-13646&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-13646&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. KRaft currently checks CREATE on the topic resource. It should be ALTER. This will be fixed in trunk as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13646&quot; title=&quot;Implement KIP-801: KRaft authorizer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-13646&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-13646&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but it would be good to fix for 3.0 and 3.1 as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note this does not affect zookeeper-based clusters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
