                            <comment id="17489845" author="hachikuji" created="Wed, 9 Feb 2022 22:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another minor difference in behavior is that KRaft allows CREATE on the Cluster resource. This is not allowed in zk clusters and was not documented by KIP-195: &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-195%3A+AdminClient.createPartitions&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-195%3A+AdminClient.createPartitions&lt;/a&gt;. Probably not a big deal to allow this, but I&apos;m inclined nevertheless to drop it for consistency.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
